HEADWORD: Onondagas
<hw>On`on*da"gas</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>; <sing>sing.
<singw>Onondaga</singw> <pr>(<?/)</pr></sing>. <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld>
<def>A tribe of Indians formerly inhabiting what is now a part of the
State of New York. They were the central or head tribe of the Five
Nations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

